# alicloud\_rds\_character\_set\_names

This data source is the character set supported by querying RDS instances.

-> **NOTE:** Available in v1.198.0+.

## Example Usage

```python
import constructs as constructs
import cdktf as cdktf
# Provider bindings are generated by running cdktf get.
# See https://cdk.tf/provider-generation for more details.
import ...gen.providers.alicloud as alicloud
class MyConvertedCode(cdktf.TerraformStack):
    def __init__(self, scope, name):
        super().__init__(scope, name)
        data_alicloud_rds_character_set_names_names =
        alicloud.data_alicloud_rds_character_set_names.DataAlicloudRdsCharacterSetNames(self, "names",
            engine="MySQL"
        )
        cdktf.TerraformOutput(self, "first_rds_character_set_names",
            value=cdktf.property_access(data_alicloud_rds_character_set_names_names.names, ["0"
            ])
        )
```

## Argument Reference

The following arguments are supported:

* `engine` - (Required, ForceNew) Database type. Options are `MySQL`, `SQLServer`, `PostgreSQL`, `MariaDB`.

## Argument Reference

The following attributes are exported in addition to the arguments listed above:

* `names` - The list of supported character sets.
